      "content": "it just feels so dishonest though. like, if you knew for a fact that a house was going to burn down in an hour, would you really sit there and try to enjoy the \"genuine experience\" of drinking a cup of tea? it feels like just prolonging the inevitable misery. honestly, if the outcome is just pain and loss, then isn't there actually a kind of peace in just... not being a part of it anymore? like, why stay for the crash?",
